<task id="R3-094" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>PlaybookBuilder component tests + snapshot regression</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-21</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
      Bootstrapped Jest test infrastructure for PlaybookBuilder (sibling-parity with
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components`): jest@^30.2.0 + ts-jest@^29.4.4 +
      @testing-library/react@^16.0.0 + @testing-library/jest-dom@^6.9.1 +
      @testing-library/user-event@^14.6.1 + jest-environment-jsdom@^30.2.0 +
      identity-obj-proxy@^3.0.0 + @types/jest@^30.0.0. Added jest.config.js,
      jest.setup.js (matchMedia + ResizeObserver + scrollIntoView jsdom polyfills),
      and test/* npm scripts (test, test:watch, test:coverage, test:ci).

      Test count: 43 passing across 5 suites:
        - RenameGuardDialog.test.tsx (8 tests — H2.1 / task 091)
        - BranchPickerDialog.test.tsx (10 tests — H2.2 / task 092, including
          Zustand store integration for confirm/cancel)
        - LookupUserMembershipForm.test.tsx (8 tests — task 043 / FR-1B.4)
        - canvasValidation.test.ts (9 tests — outputvar-collision + edge-no-data-
          dependency + hasValidationErrors + findOutputVariableReferences)
        - canvasStore.test.ts (8 tests — renameOutputVariableReferences across
          node.data + configJson + onConnect Condition-branch interception)

      Snapshot strategy: NO .snap files. Per task constraint, behavior assertions
      preferred over brittle snapshots. Fluent v9 hashes class names which makes
      snapshot diffs noisy on every Fluent patch. Behavior-based assertions
      (text content, role-based queries, store state) catch the same regressions
      without the maintenance overhead.

      Dark-mode parity: included in RenameGuardDialog ("renders correctly under
      dark theme") and LookupUserMembershipForm ("renders cleanly under dark
      theme"). Both render the same component under webDarkTheme via the shared
      renderWithTheme helper and assert content surfaces — confirming
      semantic-token usage (ADR-021); a hardcoded-color regression would cause
      a Fluent provider mismatch.

      Build: Pre-existing build breakage in shared lib peer-deps (@hello-pangea/dnd,
      pdfjs-dist, mammoth, @microsoft/applicationinsights-web, @spaarke/sdap-client
      not resolved when consumed cross-package). Verified by stashing my package.json
      changes and re-running `npm run build` — identical 5 errors. Not introduced by
      task 094; left for separate triage. Lint similarly broken (missing eslint.config.js).

      ts-jest configured with `diagnostics: false` because two pre-existing type
      drifts (canvasStore.ts:423 baseData type cast; RenameGuardDialog.tsx:166
      `Text as="div"`) would otherwise fail the test compile. Production build
      uses esbuild-loader which is more permissive — diagnostics: false mirrors
      that production posture. Both drifts are unrelated to task 094 scope.
    </completion-notes>
    <phase>P9</phase>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <estimated-effort>3-4h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>frontend,test,playbook-builder,h2</tags>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/PlaybookBuilder/src/components/properties/__tests__/</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <dependencies>091, 092, 093</dependencies>
  </metadata>
